---------------------------------------------------------------------
Railroad Earth is a roots and Americana-based jamband from Stillwater, NJ. 
Their name stems from a Jack Kerouac poem "October in the Railroad Earth," 
and the band has a song by the same name. Railroad Earth's music combines 
elements of bluegrass, rock and roll, jazz, celtic and more, and the group is 
known for its extensive live improvisation and lyrical songwriting within an 
acoustic base. The Amen Corner album features songs such as "Been Down 
This Road," "Waggin' The Dog," and "Lovin' You."
